Sentencas: The perovskite La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-delta (LSCCu) oxide is synthesized by a modified Pechini method and examined as a novel cathode material for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) based upon functional graded anode.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode

Sentencas: The perovskite LSCCu exhibits excellent ionic and electronic conductivities in the intermediate-to-low-temperature range (400-800 C).
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode

Sentencas: Thin Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte and NiO-SDC anode functional layer are prepared over macroporous anode Substrates composed of NiO-SDC by a one-step dry-pressing/co-firing process.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode

Sentencas: A single cell with 20 mu m thick SDC electrolyte on a porous anode support and LSCCu-SDC cathode shows peak power densities of only 583.2 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C and 309.4 mW cm(-2) for 550 degrees C
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode

Sentencas: While a cell with 20 mu m thick SDC electrolyte and ail anode functional layer on the macroporous anode substrate shows peak power densities of 867.3 and 490.3 mW cm(-2) at 650 and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode

Sentencas: The dramatic improvement of cell performance is attributed to the much improved anode microstructure that is confirmed by both SEM observation and impedance spectroscopy The results indicate that LSCCu is a very promising cathode material for LT-SOFCs and the one-step dry-pressing/co-firing process is a suitable technique to fabricate high performance SOFCs.
Titulo: Low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with novel La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Cu0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode and functional graded anode
